history.content:
As EECS, you'll most likely be able to get a spot in 16B. Given that anyone can take EE 126, I'd suggest definetely including 126 in your phase 1. Depending on how popular the AC class is(assume that the higher the average grade is on Berkeleytime, the more likely it could be taken), I would phase 1 that possibly.

As for Math 54, It seems a bit redundant because you already took EE 16A. Maybe take another class like CS 188 or another fairly chill class.

****

I would actually say that you should phase 1 16b in order to get the lab section you want. If lab times aren't a priority for you, I would phase 2 that. I would definitely phase 2 math 54, although I would actually think that math 54 isn't a necessary class for you since you are enrolling in 16b, but that's up to you.

Depending on how popular the AC class is(assume that the higher the average grade is on Berkeleytime, the more likely it could be taken), I would phase 1 that possibly.

As for Math 54, It seems a bit redundant because you already took EE 16A. Maybe take another class like CS 188 or another fairly chill class.

The first three are very specific, there's only one course you can take to fulfill the requirement. Thus, I was phase 1 them. There are many courses that can fulfill AC, so it might be a safer bet to phase 2. just my thoughts.
